==English==

===Noun===
'''Picture Sorts'''  

#(Advertising) a research tool used to deconstruct the audience’s visual experience of a television commercial.
#:'''''Picture Sorts''' are the tools most useful to the ad team because it shows them, in pictures instead of words, what is and is not working in the ad.''
#(Advertising) a research tool used to diagnose different strengths and weaknesses of the commercial via [[flow of attention|Flow of Attention]], [[flow of emotion|Flow of Emotion]], and [[flow of meaning|Flow of Meaning]].



===References===
''The Advertising Research Handbook'' Charles E. Young, Ideas in Flight, Seattle, WA, April 2005